String methods in JS --
let st = "Hello" -- 
st.charAt( ) ; 
.indexOf( ) -- index of first occurence of the letter
.lastIndexOf( ) -- last index of
.length -- not method -- returns length of string
.trim() --- removes whitespaces after or before the string
.toLowercase()    .toUppercase()    .repeat(3) -- repeat the same string 3 times.
.startsWith(`H`) -- returns boolean , .endsWith() , .includes()
.replaceAll("a" , "b") -- replaces all a's with b's
.padstart(a , "0") -- adds padding to the string -- a = desired length of the string. and 0 is the character used to pad the string.
.padEnd(a , "0") -- adds padding to the end of the string.

** Using `print()` in JS -- prints the web page.

STRING SPLICING --
string.slice(0.4); -- starting index , ending index 
string.slice(-1) -- starts at the ending index. and on decreasing the index further it moves towards the back.

string.slice(0 , string.indexOf("A")); -- ending index is the first index where the character A is found.

Method chaining --
Calling one mathod after naother in one continuous line of code.
let username = "  roNItdeY  ";
username = username.trim().charAt(0).toUpperCase() + username.trim().slice(username.charAt(0)+1).toLowerCase();
console.log(username);
-- easier but can be complex when too long.

